      "text": "Have you ever walked aroundConnectionsand wondered,where are my people?Well, now you know exactly where they are. For the first time, we will have a dedicated Connections Community Hub space for marketers, by marketers. Connections will June 11-12 in Chicago. The Community Hub will be by the registration desk in Campground, Level 3. This space will only feature content from Trailblazers. There will be 40+ sessions, including: Mitigating the Disaster that is Dark Mode to Accessibility for EmailsDedicated IPs for Low Volume SendersEmail A/B Testing: Prioritize, Progress, and PerfectMarketing Yourself: Why Your Brand Is Your Best ChannelCommerce Without Chaos: Best Practices for Team Alignment There will be an emphasis onskill developmentwith the goal of helping marketers get better at their jobs. Want to learn why your personal brand is your most powerful channel for building credibility and attracting new opportunities? Want your emails to always reach the inbox? These questions and more will be answered by experiencedTrailblazersin the hub. We will have a number of meetups for attendees to network, exchange ideas, and carry ideas beyond the sessions. And there will be fun activities such as a breakfast with Salesforce leaders, a networking social, carnival-style games with prizes, frozen drink stations, a community give-back activity, and an ice cream social. Whether you’re looking to deepen knowledge, build your network or share your passion with like-minded individuals the Community Hub is for you. Read on for details on speakers and times. See you there!",
